d require more skills and equipment, but they also offer more freedom and adventure.Lead climbing involves climbing routes without a fixed rope and attaching your rope to carabiners (metal loops) attached to the rock as you climb.Traditional climbing involves climbing routes without pre-placed protections and placing your own gear (such as nuts and cams) into cracks and holes in the rock as you climb.Rock climbing is a rewarding and exciting sport that can enrich your life in many ways.`

